<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 2812/94 of 18 November 1994 amending Council Regulation (EEC) No 1101/89 as regards the conditions which apply to the putting into service of new capacity in inland waterway transport </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2812/94, millega muudetakse n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1101/89 siseveetranspordis uue kandev&otilde;ime kasutuselev&otilde;tu suhtes kehtivate tingimuste osas 18. november 1994 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1101/89 of 27 April 1989 on structural improvements in inland waterway transport (1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 844/94 (2), and in particular Article 8 (1) (c) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 27. aprilli 1994. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 1101/89 siseveetranspordi struktuurilise t&otilde;hustamise kohta, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 844/94, eriti selle artikli 8 l&otilde;ike 1 punkti c, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in recent years, the market trend in inland waterway transport has been unfavourable; whereas it has become apparent that, because it is possible to have vessels built at low cost in third countries, the ratio between the new tonnage and the old tonnage referred to in Article 8 (1) (a) of Regulation (EEC) No 1101/89, currently 1: 1, does not exercise sufficient control over the emergence of new overcapacity, thereby jeopardizing the effects of Community scrapping measures; whereas, therefore, that ratio should be adjusted; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: siseveetranspordituru suundumus on viimastel aastatel olnud ebasoodne; on selgunud, et t&auml;nu v&otilde;imalusele lasta laevu odavalt ehitada kolmandates riikides, ei piisa m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1101/89 artikli 8 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis a nimetatud uue ja vana tonnaa&zcaron;i vahelisest suhtest, mis praegu on 1: 1, uue &uuml;lemahutavuse tekke piisavaks kontrollimiseks, ja seet&otilde;ttu n&otilde;rgeneb &uuml;henduse lammutusmeetmete m&otilde;ju; nimetatud suhet tuleks seet&otilde;ttu kohandada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas provision should be made, by way of a transitional arrangement, for the 1: 1 ratio to continue to apply to vessels whose construction has reached a certain stage and which are put into service within six months of the entry into force of the abovementioned adjustment; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks s&auml;testada &uuml;leminekukord, mille alusel suhet 1: 1 kohaldataks ka edaspidi laevadele, mille ehitus on j&otilde;udnud teatud etappi ja mis v&otilde;etakse kasutusele kuue kuu jooksul alates eespool nimetatud kohanduse j&otilde;ustumisest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measure set out in this Regulation has been the subject of consultations with the Member States and with organizations representing the inland waterway sector, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetme puhul on peetud n&otilde;u liikmesriikide ning siseveetranspordi sektorit esindavate organisatsioonidega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The three indents appearing in Article 8 (1) (a) of Regulation (EEC) No 1101/89 are replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1101/89 artikli 8 l&otilde;ike 1 punkti a kolm esimest taanet asendatakse j&auml;rgmistega: </eesti>
<inglise> '- the owner of the vessel to be brought into service scraps a tonnage of carrying capacity equivalent to one and a half times that of the new vessel, or </inglise>
<eesti> "- kasutuselev&otilde;etava laeva omanik lammutab vanametalliks sellise tonnaa&zcaron;i kandev&otilde;imest, mis on poolteist korda suurem uue laeva tonnaa&zcaron;ist, v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - where the owner scraps no vessel, he pays into the Fund covering his new vessel or into the Fund chosen by him in accordance with article 4 a special contribution equal to the scrapping premium fixed for a tonnage equal to one and a half times that of the new vessel, or </inglise>
<eesti> - omanik ei lammuta &uuml;htegi laeva vanametalliks, aga maksab fondi, mille ta on valinud artikli 4 kohaselt, erilist osamaksu, mis on samav&auml;&auml;rne uue laeva tonnaa&zcaron;ist poolteist korda suurema tonnaa&zcaron;i puhul m&auml;&auml;ratud vanametalliks lammutamise h&uuml;vitisega, v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - where the owner scraps a tonnage smaller than one and a half times that of the new vessel to be brought into service, he pays into the Fund in question a special contibution equivalent to the scrapping premium corresponding at the time to the difference between one and a half times the tonnage of the new vessel and the tonnage scrapped. </inglise>
<eesti> - juhul, kui omanik lammutab vanametalliks tonnaa&zcaron;i, mis on v&auml;iksem kui kasutuselev&otilde;etava uue laeva poolteistkordne tonnaa&zcaron;, maksab ta k&otilde;nealusesse fondi erilist osamaksu, mis v&otilde;rdub tol hetkel uue laeva poolteistkordse tonnaa&zcaron;i ja vanametalliks lammutatava tonnaa&zcaron;i erinevusele vastavale vanametalliks lammutamise h&uuml;vitisele." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> For vessels in respect of which the owner proves that: </inglise>
<eesti> Laevade suhtes, mille kohta omanik t&otilde;endab, et: </eesti>
<inglise> - construction was underway on the date of publication of this Regulation, and that </inglise>
<eesti> - k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse avaldamise kuup&auml;eval neid juba ehitati ja </eesti>
<inglise> - work already carried out by the date of publication of this Regulation represents at least 20 % of the steel weight or 50 tonnes, and that </inglise>
<eesti> - k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse avaldamise kuup&auml;evaks tehtud t&ouml;&ouml; vastab v&auml;hemalt 20%le tarvitatava terase massist v&otilde;i 50 tonnile ja </eesti>
<inglise> - delivery and commissioning is to take place within the six months following the entry into force of this Regulation, </inglise>
<eesti> - &uuml;leandmine ja kasutuselev&otilde;tt toimub kuue kuu jooksul p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse j&otilde;ustumist, </eesti>
<inglise> the conditions set out in Article 8 (1) (a) of Regulation (EEC) No 1101/89, as they applied before the entry into force of this Regulation, shall continue to apply, on request to the authorities of the Fund covering the vessel. </inglise>
<eesti> kohaldatakse m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1101/89 artikli 8 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis a s&auml;testatud tingimusi, nagu neid kohaldati enne k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse j&otilde;ustumist, kui vastav taotlus esitatakse selle fondi p&auml;devale instantsile, kuhu laev kuulub. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the 20th day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub 20. p&auml;eval p&auml;rast Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 18 November 1994. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 18. november 1994 </eesti>
<inglise> For the Commission Marcelino OREJA Member of the Commission </inglise>
